---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SchemaMarkup from '../../components/SchemaMarkup.astro';
import Icon from '../../components/Icon.astro';

const publishDate = "July 2026";
const lastUpdated = "July 2026";
const author = "Todd Frederickson";
const readTime = "11 min read";

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Is Bear Brothers Cleaning good?",
    answer: "Yes. Bear Brothers Cleaning is an established, professional Huntsville-based company with real staff and a footprint across seven cities, from Huntsville and Madison down to Birmingham and Bessemer. If you want a company with an established local presence and strong Birmingham-area coverage, they're a solid choice. The Valley Clean Team is the better fit if you want a flat written quote within two hours, photo proof of every clean, and the same team each visit."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does Bear Brothers Cleaning cost?",
    answer: "Bear Brothers Cleaning doesn't publish flat starting prices, so cost depends on your home and the service you book. The Valley Clean Team publishes its floor up front: standard and recurring cleans from $176, deep cleans from $276, quoted in writing before you book. If knowing the price before anyone walks your home matters to you, that transparency is the difference."
  },
  {
    question: "What's the best cleaning service in Huntsville, AL?",
    answer: "There isn't a single best — it depends on what you're optimizing for. For an established company with wide North Alabama and Birmingham-area coverage, Bear Brothers Cleaning is a strong pick. For a written flat quote in about two hours, photo proof of the finished clean, the same team every visit, and a women-led, veteran-owned team, The Valley Clean Team fits better. Both are professional operations, so the choice comes down to service model, not quality alone."
  },
  {
    question: "Bear Brothers Cleaning vs an independent cleaner — which is better?",
    answer: "An established company like Bear Brothers offers wider coverage and staffing depth than most solo independents. A vetted team like The Valley Clean Team sits between the two: small enough to guarantee the same crew every visit and let you text the owner directly, but insured, bonded, and background-checked the way a lone independent often isn't. The insurance gap is the one that matters most — it rules out uninsured solo cleaners and gig-app marketplaces on risk alone."
  },
  {
    question: "Do these cleaning companies carry insurance and a guarantee?",
    answer: "Bear Brothers is a legitimate, professional operation. The Valley Clean Team carries $2 million in liability coverage, is bonded, and every team member is background-checked. We also send post-clean photos the day of the clean, so you can flag anything before you pay rather than after. If insurance depth and documented proof are your priorities, ask any company you're considering to put its coverage in writing."
  },
  {
    question: "Does Bear Brothers Cleaning serve Birmingham?",
    answer: "Yes — Birmingham and Bessemer are a genuine strength for Bear Brothers, alongside their Huntsville base and coverage of Madison, Decatur, Athens, Florence, and Muscle Shoals. The Valley Clean Team also serves the Birmingham area, including Mountain Brook. If you're in Mountain Brook or greater Birmingham and want a flat two-hour written quote with photo proof, we cover it; if you want the company with the longest-standing Birmingham-area presence, that's Bear Brothers."
  }
];
